Preheat your #oven{} to 190 degrees. Put two #pots{} of water on to boil with @salt{1/4%tsp}. Peel and chop the @potatoes{5}(peeled and chopped) into golf ball sized chunks. Chop the very top and bottom from the @green beans{1}(top and tailed).

Grate @courgettes{3}(grated) and squeeze out excess liquid with your hands. Spread out the grated and drained courgettes between sheets of #paper towel{} to be assured of a delicious crunchy topping.

> Moist courgettes will result in a crust that is soggy instead of crisp and golden.

Put your potatoes into one of the pots of boiling water. Cook them for around ~{10-15%minutes} or until you can easily slip a knife through them. After ~{5%minutes} of cooking your potatoes, boil your green beans in the other #pot{} for around ~{8%minutes} or until cooked.

Sandwich your @British chicken breasts{4} between two pieces of #cling film{} and lay on your #chopping board{}. Pound each chicken breast quite firmly with a #mallet{}, #rolling pin{} or something else heavy.

> By flattening the chicken to just over a cm thick you will cut down on the cooking time.

In a #small bowl{} mix the grated courgettes with the finely grated @Pecorino cheese{to taste}(finely grated). Mix in the @chilli flakes{1}(adjust to taste). Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

> The chilli flakes are spicy, so add less if the little 'uns don't like it!

Coat each chicken breast in @oil{1/2%tsp} and place on a #baking tray{}. Spoon on the courgette mixture thickly, making sure it's compact and covers all the chicken. Place in hot oven for ~{15%minutes} or until slightly crispy on top.

> After 15 mins put the chicken under a very hot grill until the top is nicely crisped all over.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain the water from them. Put the potatoes back on the hob for ~{1%minute} to dry them out and add a lump of @?butter{1%lump}. Mash the butter into the potatoes with a #potato masher{} (you can also add a dash of @?milk{dash}). When the potatoes are smooth season well with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Lay your courgette-covered chicken on a bed of potato mash with your green beans on the side. Finish with a @lemon{1%wedge} on top.